text:
Proposing a copyleft license for Snapchain 

We need to release Snapchain under an open source license for people to be able to use the code safely. We're proposing using GPL v3, which is a copy left license. 

This means that you can use, modify and redistribute it freely as long as any changes are also made public and available to all.

a reminder that while you can of course tag me to chat in public, we also have a Neynar AI companion miniapp (that's open to all Farcaster users regardless of your score!)

https://farcaster.xyz/miniapps/w1O_146jGEE9/neynar-ai

cast.text:
now there's a @neynar AI companion app

I like that it didn't ask to be added as a mini-app until AFTER  you asked a question.

The response it gave me on whether I should bother trying to improve my neynar score:

Your Neynar score reflects your reputation and trustworthiness on Farcaster, based on your activity and interactions. Scores close to 1 (like your 0.97) are already excellent.

**Can you improve it?**  
Maybe—by continuing to engage positively, avoiding spammy behavior, and building genuine connections. However, since you’re already at 0.97, any changes will likely be small.

**Is it worth it?**  
There’s usually no practical benefit in pushing from 0.97 to 1.0. Most features and mini apps look for users above a certain trust threshold (often 0.85–0.9), which you already surpass. Gaming the system isn’t recommended—organic activity is best.

Bottom line: You’re in great standing! Focus on authentic participation rather than trying to “optimize” your score.

text:
@tipn campaigns deliver measurable results for token projects. 

Here's the data from the recent @betrmint campaign, which was guided by Quotient analytics.
- Every $1 in $BETR distributed by the campaign drove $4+ dollars in buy volume
- Average daily buy volume jumped from $5,000 the week before the campaign was announced, to $26,000 in the run-up to and during the campaign 
- $400+ new holders, who bought on average $110 of BETR
- These new holders are high quality, with a median Farcaster Cred Score of .66, which corresponds to the top 2,300 users on Farcaster 

We work closely with the @tipn team to optimize campaign allocations to make sure incentives go to authentic + aligned users and not farmers.

Reach out to @ruminations or @niftytime.eth if you're interested in running a comment tipping campaign for your project!

List of projects I’ve coded for GM Farcaster:

1) the OG @warpee.eth , an AI bot who will answer your questions using its knowledge about @gmfarcaster 

2) the GM Farcaster miniapp so you can watch our live stream or latest episode without leaving the app miniapp.gmfarcaster.com

3) a lore explorer which shows every cast we’ve featured on @gmfarcaster and lets you search to see yours lore.gmfarcaster.com 

4) our main informational website gmfarcaster.com

5) a media kit with information for potential sponsors mediakit.gmfarcaster.com

I was a software engineer in the early 2000s but when I got into people management I stopped coding. I took a web3 dev course in 2022 which was my first time getting back into hands on coding in 15 years, and only with AI copilots have I been able to do so much for @gmfarcaster 

I’ve learned a ton this past year and look forward to continuing to iterate and build and learn

text:
Thank You.

I should have been asleep in my bed 2 hrs ago but i'm up because i'm kinda overwhelmed with feelings and you know if someone gives me good vibes -> i always share them back. I always give back because I appreciate it. That’s why I'm here, sharing this with y'all.

I don't think I can express how much I'm grateful for this opportunity and I'm so happy that you are supporting me. That means so fkn much.

As I said earlier, I have grand plans for this one. I'm not here to shill or run narratives or other bs (i've seen a lot of stuff and i've been rugged a few times because i was a hard believer). Just putting out what’s on my mind right now.

I don't have many public projects, I don't have famous or recognizable collabs. I'm just here -> another human you see on the Internet. Here's the thing -> we need to appreciate raw feelings more, respect and support each other. I believed, believe and will believe in this vision. That's why I'm building Pet Rock Life. This is not an investment. These are rocks.

I hope I won't let y'all down. I just want to bring some positive energy here with my little creation. I created a token to fund this project, probably I will need to assemble a team or something since I'm a solo dev. Maybe not now, but in the future.

Tokens are locked until 1 December 2025, and will be vested until 1 January 2026. I locked 17% supply because it seems reasonable to me -> most of these tokens will go on funding the project. I'm currently full-time working on PRL right now. Yeah, simply speaking -> if you believe in me -> you can buy some to support me. Please don't expect gains. You can lose money.

Finally ->
And I wonder if you know
What it means to find your dreams come true

$ROCK 🪨

show_title: From Likes to Coins—How CoBuild Prints Tokens in Your Sleep: GM Farcaster ep283
text:
Let me address this so you all can know a bit more about trading world. If you see a wallet that only sells with no buys -> it can simply mean that some traders are trying to hide their activity or something else. You also need to understand the concept of copy trading. When some famous wallet buys something -> it gets immediately copy traded. There is even a functionality for this on Interface if you didn't know.

This is the first point.

Secondly, let me clarify the launch details. I'm not affiliated with anyone, and I have no team at all. I can provide all proofs if absolutely necessary. $ROCK is a stealth launch (launched 7d ago), announced first on @petrock account. You can prove that (no one bought before this cast, only the sniper and me with my first buy). Stop calling it insider trading. Anyone who was following at that time could buy this token when it was low mcap (if you WANT to make gains on it). Stop accusing me of this bs. I don't want to be related to it.

I won't be replying to every 'scam' accusation because it's very normal to me. There were a lot of scams and other stuff in crypto, so no token or a project can pass without these accusations. The thing is that I'm here standing for my reputation and public image. People just don't understand how crypto works and someone even think that they supposed to buy this token or I ask them to buy it. If you think I'm a scammer -> then don't buy it. It's crystal clear.

Sad for me to see people who I thought were genuinely good people and even supported PRL now calling me a scammer because some trader takes profits on it from his empty wallets
